<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The low bits require touching in 3 cases:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#42; A non-immediate value will always require both instructions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#42; An effectively imm13 value needs only an &#39;or&#39; instruction.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#42; Otherwise, an immediate that is not effectively imm13 requires the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   &#39;or&#39; only if bits remain after clearing the 22 bits that &#39;sethi&#39; set.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If the low bits are known zeros, there&#39;s nothing to do.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// In the second case, and only in that case, must we NOT clear</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// bits of the immediate value via the %lo() assembler function.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Note also, the &#39;or&#39; instruction doesn&#39;t mind a large value in the case</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// where the operand to &#39;set&#39; was 0xFFFFFzzz - it does exactly what you mean.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (!IsImm || IsEffectivelyImm13 || (ImmValue &amp; 0x3ff)) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (IsEffectivelyImm13)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"><Highlight kind="normal">      Expr = ValExpr;</Highlight></CodeLine>
